reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Rusted within hours
reviews.reviewText: Very disappointed with this product. I poured a kettle of boiling water in it, measured the temp, it was 203°F, 5 hours and 50 minutes later, it went down to 132°F. Not only that, a rust spot formed as well - see pic. It's not at the seam, but at the bottom inside of the jug. I ordered this to replace another 64oz jug that I have that rusted at the seam after a few years of use, so I thought this might be a good replacement, but it wasn't even 6 hours, it already rusted. Really regret getting this. What's worse is that this is a vine item, I'm not allowed to communicate with the seller to ask for a replacement. Total waste of money!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars My water stay so cold
reviews.reviewText: I love the color of my water bottle and that my water stay cold up to 48 hrs honestly. I love that it came with two lids but I only use one everyday. It’s super easy to clean even though I only put water in it. Money well spent !

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 10, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars BIG and sturdy
reviews.reviewText: Gifted this to my son for Christmas. He loved it. He and his wife both keep water bottles with them at all times. This tough bottle will survive getting banged around by their kids. Plus, the design isn’t hard to clean. Huge capacity - absolutely will NOT fit in your car’s cup holder.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 6, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars High quality. Good hand-feel. Large capacity.
reviews.reviewText: I use this bottle for gym and travel. It is large enough but not too heavy. The surface provides a good grip and is not slippery, which is an excellent feature. This bottle comes with two different tops, which fits my different needs in different places.The quality is surprisingly high given the price is so affordable. I have recommended it to several friends.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars my wife loves it
reviews.reviewText: I have a tumbler addiction and i think eveyone should have a tumbler. Unfortunately, she's getting caught in the crossfire of my addiction at first she wasnt really with it, then she started to open up to it, and since this tumbler, she is all in. she takes it to work every day and doesnt use any other tumbler now. she loves this one. she says it keeps her drinks cold her entire shift and shes a nurse so her shifts range from 8 hours to 20 a day.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Good bottle and rugged. Retains cold and heat well. Gaskets keep a good seal. I use it everyday. I dropped it on the pavement and the finish, metal, and plastic were unscathed. This is as good as the high end bottles.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Super solid, wide mouth bottle with a weird straw...
reviews.reviewText: Got this for my daughter for all-day softball tournaments. For that purpose, we end up filling it often from hotel ice machines, and this bottle is great for that - the mouth is very wide and it holds a lot of water. Its also very sturdily built - the handle is heavy aluminum that looks like it will take a lot of abuse. It does *not* have an ability to hook onto a fence like other bottles of this size I've seen - it just has the loop handle.The lid screws shut securely, and it comes with two straws. But the straws are weird; they just sort of sit in the opening. I guess that's so you can use the bottle by tipping it up and drink out of the spout? But i'm used to the straw being an integral part of flip up lid, and the straw attaching permanently. Here it just sort of flops around in the opening (see pic), and when you shut the lid it squishes it out of the way. I guess its fine, but i'm sure that given that the straw isn't attached it will get lost/bent/broken. Shrug.
